C. TRIPLE NECESSITY FRAMEWORK
The Triple Necessity Framework combines disability, attorney non-responsiveness, and imminent financial harm to establish maximum legal protection for unilateral actions. This framework applies when:

Medical necessity exists (PTSD/ADHD disability, income loss, insurance termination)
Financial necessity exists (exhaustion of resources, bridge loan, imminent foreclosure)
